VDR Plugin 'statusleds' Revision History
----------------------------------------

2025-09-06: Version 0.7

- partly revert 'stop the plugin properly'
- more dsyslog
- include fcntl

2025-05-30: Version 0.6

- stop the plugin properly
- change led at Save()
- preset PrewarnBeeps to 0

2024-09-14: Version 0.5

- remove blinkd, because it doesn't exit any more
- fix prewarn beep
- close file descriptor

2024-09-12: Version 0.4

- convert old Makefile and internationalization to the new style
- patch for vdr
- use IRMP_STM32's status led
- turn LEDs on at start of VDR; turn LEDs off, when VDR stops; let LEDs blink, if VDR is recording
- cTimer is const since vdr-2.3.1 and requires locking since vdr-2.3.2
- vdr-1.3.47 requires APIVERSION instead of VDRVERSION

2006-01-20: Version 0.3

- Adding -fPIC to the compiler options
- Make it compatible with vdr >= 1.3.38

2004-11-22: Version 0.2

- Fixed Makefile error

2004-11-22: Version 0.1

- Fixed includes (missing vdr prefix) (thanks to Tobias Grimm)
- Buffer for blinkd host now 256 bytes (thanks to Tobias Grimm)
- Shorter version numbering

2004-02-02: Version 0.0.7

- Presignaling of recordings with console beeps

2004-01-25: Version 0.0.6

- The OSD settings for using blinkd and per record blinking are now
  taken correctly from setup.conf (thanks to Heiko Meyer).

2004-01-07: Version 0.0.5

- Plugin now compiles for vdr-1.3.0

2003-11-12: Version 0.0.4

- Now it's possible to use blinkd for remote signaling

2003-09-03: Version 0.0.3

- Inserted some missing command line argument handling
- New command line argument "-c console"

2003-09-01: Version 0.0.2

- Fixed crash at vdr stop


2003-08-22: Version 0.0.1

- Initial revision.
